result.name: Coffee by Zion

reviews.text:
Unexpected find right outside of the Sai Ying Pun B2 exit. Quality of food was much better in quality and execution than those large food group chains you find next to the tram way. Didn't get to try the coffee this time but will return for sure. 

Recommended to those who enjoy the cafe scene and brunch foods but would rather support local businesses and prefer something more intimate .
A little pricey but totally worth it. Excellent coffee and food. Great ambiance.

Quiet Café in a very accessible location. Comfy, laid-back ambience.  Easygoing forthcoming staff. The cappuccino is strong and has a nutty note. The matcha is not sweet (which is good) and has a pronounced and delicious green tea note. Overall a commendable experience.
The best breakfast in sai yin pun ...hongkong.. their breakfast variation menu are so delicious..must try them all..their coffee is also good nowadays...

Lovely coffeeshop with good quality food, tea and coffee. The vegetarian brunch option was generous. Not the biggest place (bigger than the hideout though), but makes good use of available space. You can also sit outside. Nice to relax with a friend over a cup of coffee. Sai Ying Pun needs more places like this!
